[1] France (Fatalities)
Date: Tue 22 Jan 2013
Source: Top Actus Sante [in French, trans. Mod.CP, edited]
http://topactu.fr/sante/la-rougeole-a-fait-6-morts-en-france/18855/2013/01/22.html


More than 23 000 cases of measles including 6 deaths were reported in France between 1 Jan 2008 and 16 Jan 2013, according to data released by l'Institut de Veille Sanitaire (The Institute of Public Health). Measles virus, which is transmitted easily because of its persistence in the air and or on surfaces contaminated with nasopharyngeal secretions, continues to circulate throughout France with the greatest incidence observed in the southwest.

This highly contagious viral infection continues to claim lives in France, according to figures released by l'Institut de Veille Sanitaire. Approximately 14 966 cases were reported in 2011 and 6 deaths. Last year [2012], 859 cases were reported without a significant epidemic peak in the spring as might have been expected. Among these patients, there were 3 cases of encephalitis and 32 cases of severe pneumonia.

L'Institut de Veille Sanitaire calls for enhanced surveillance. France must continue to ensure that all those born after 1980 receive 2 doses of the MMR (mumps, measles and rubella) vaccine. As a member of the European Region of the World Health Organization, France has a commitment to eliminate measles and congenital rubella infection.

