[7] Pakistan (Balochistan, Punjab, Sindh)
Date: Mon 21 Jan 2013
Source: Dawn [edited]
http://dawn.com/2013/01/21/4-more-children-die-of-measles/


A deadly measles outbreak has left at least 4 more children dead, mounting the death toll to 459 across the country, while 429 children have died in Sindh [province] alone. According to reports gathered from different parts of Sindh [province], 2 children died in Kandhkot during the last 24 hours, raising the overall toll for the district to 157. Among the most-affected cities, 84 are in Sukkur, 55 in Shikarpur, 50 in Khairpur, 33 in Ghotki, 14 in Thul, 8 in Larkana, while 4 children died of measles in Hyderabad.

In Punjab [province], 15 children have died of measles since the outbreak gripped the province. Four children died in Dera Ghazi Khan, while measles claimed 7 lives in Rajanpur, Ahmedpur, Sharqia, Liaqatpur, Taxila, and Hujra Shah Muqeem.

Meanwhile, 10 children have died in Balochistan [province], while measles claimed 5 lives in Mohmand Agency.

